key_points: This is a preprint submitted to the arXiv repository.
The subject area is high energy physics - experiment (hep-ex).

section: Dark Matter Induced Neutron Production Search Limits
key_points: An indirect detection search for dark matter is performed using neutron production data.
The NMDS-II detector was used for 1440 hours at 1166 m.w.e. and 6504 hours at 583 m.w.e.
The detector consists of a 30 cm cube Pb-target with 60 3He neutron counters.
The highest neutron multiplicity event observed was 54 neutrons.
Two DM-M interaction models (spallation and fireball) were used to set limits.
Spin-independent limits are at the level of 10−45 cm2, and spin-dependent limits are at 2 × 10−42 cm2.
